Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower 
Share prices on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday.
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 6.75 points
to 665.26, the all-share Emas Index dropped 1.60 points to 153.12, the
Industrial Index fell 13.34 points to 1,199.03 and the Second Board
Index dipped 1.71 points to 111.27.
Losers led gainers by 520 to 99 while 155 counters were unchanged and
255 others untraded.
The day's turnover increased to 90.297 million shares valued at 172.297
million ringgit (45.34 million U.S. dollars) from 67.939 million shares
worth 116.475 million ringgit (30.65 million dollars) last Friday.
